title.narrative: Pan-Commonwealth Natural Resources Advisory Assistance for Sustainable Development

description.narrative: Many Commonwealth member countries lack the legal; taxation and revenue management; environmental policies and systems to ensure that natural resource wealth leads to sustainable economic and social development. These issues will be exacerbated by the covid-19 pandemic. How the problem will be addressed: This Project will provide direct technical assistance to 13 Commonwealth Member countries (The Bahamas, Barbados, Belize, Botswana, Cook Islands, Ghana, Guyana, Jamaica, Kiribati, Namibia, Papua New Guinea, Swaziland, and Vanuatu), to assist them better regulate and tax the natural resources sector. It will also assist these governments manage the revenue from natural resources. Outputs: Over the next four years this Project will at a minimum: draft at least 5 laws, which if enacted will lead to the superior regulation of significant and transformative economic activity design at least 4 new fiscal/tax regimes, which if implemented, will lead to billions of dollars of additional government revenue; draft at least 3 new environmental policies and regulations, which if implemented, will lead to improved environmental protection; design at least 2 sovereign wealth funds to improve the management of natural resource revenues. Value Added of the Commonwealth Secretariat's Oceans and Natural Resources Advisory Division ‘(ONR’): ONR is uniquely placed to implement this Project because of its existing relationship as trusted adviser to member countries, and the methodology of our approach: Demand Led. All outputs that are produced by this Project are demanded by Commonwealth member countries. This Project will never produce an output which isn't asked for by a country. This contrasts to other technical assistance projects which can be a difficult compromise between the priorities of the donor, the demands of the recipient and a consultancy company's desire to produce work they can charge for. Legal Drafting. This Project does not just offer policy advice. It also assists countries implement this advice by drafting laws, regulations and contracts. This is special. Most consultancy companies and international organisations that offer policy advice do not have legal drafting capability and do not undertake such work. The advice ONR offers is thus well-rounded and much more likely to be implemented and result in concrete outcomes. In addition, ONR is the only organisation to offer countries technical assistance on deep sea mining. Expertise of the Team. ONR has a highly experienced team which draws expertise from the private sector, international organisations and government. Its expertise also cuts across environmental management, legal form and economics.
